<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,760,1786,1808]" box="[151,760,1786,1808]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Species included: 7 (Afrotropical; confined to 
<collectingCountry box="[622,749,1786,1808]" name="Madagascar" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1853,2021]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Synapomorphy: Basiphallus heavily sclerotised, markedly expanded apically and narrowed pre-apically (47). 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas, L." box="[151,308,1889,1913]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="145 - 171" refId="ref108265" refString="Tsacas, L. (1977) Les Curtonotidae (Diptera) de l'Afrique: 1. Le genre Curtonotum Macquart. Annals of the Natal Museum, 23, 145 - 171." type="journal article" year="1977">Tsacas (1977)</bibRefCitation>
included all species then known from 
<collectingCountry box="[755,890,1889,1913]" name="Madagascar" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duda (PPRI" authorityYear="1935" box="[972,1112,1889,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuthbertsoni">
<emphasis box="[972,1112,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">cuthbertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. Seven of the species recorded from the island are regarded as being sufficiently distinct to warrant inclusion in a species-group of their own, as attested by the above-mentioned synapomorphy. A more complete molecular study of the Malagasy 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Macquart" authorityYear="1844" box="[267,402,1997,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Curtonotidae" genus="Curtonotum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[267,402,1997,2021]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Curtonotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna is required to ascertain whether this species-group is truly monophyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
